SUMMARY:The People’s University: America 250 – Revolution & Constitution
LOCATION:Ohio County Public Library\, 52 16th Street\, Wheeling\, WV
 26003
DESCRIPTION:Class 2: Thursday\, July 2 — 7PM – Independence Declared\,
 1775-1776 Class 3: Thursday\, July 9 — 7PM – The Double Sevens – 1777
 Class 4: Thursday\, July 16 — 7PM – The Year of the French – 1778 Class
 5: Thursday\, July 23 — 7PM – The Battle of Camden – 1779-1780 Class 6:
 Thursday\, July 30 — 7PM – Siege and Surrender -1781-1782 Class 7\,
 Thursday\, August 6 — 7PM – Foundations of Freedom – 1783-1789 Class 8:
 Thursday\, August 13 — NOON – Finale: “A Republic–if You Can Keep It.”
 Readings from the Declaration of Independence and Constitution What to
 expect at People’s University: America 250: Revolution & Constitution?
 https://www.facebook.com/peoplesuniversityOCPL Classes will also be
 livestreamed and will be available on the Lunch With Books Facebook and
 YouTube pages during and after the live event. Ohio County Public Library
